<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4347.3.1>
    bibo:endPage "445" ;
    bibo:issue "3" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2017-11-14" ;
    bibo:startPage "401" ;
    bibo:volume "4347" ;
    dc:creator "Castro-Gerardino, Diana Jimena; Llorente-Bousquets, Jorge" ;
    dc:date "2017" ;
    dc:title "Comparative exploration of antennae in Pseudopontia, and antennal clubs of the tribes Leptideini and Dismorphiini (Lepidoptera: Pieridae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048543>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048549>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048551>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048529>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048533> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048543>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. (A – D). Antennal club II of Dismorphiinae species. A. Dismorphia theucharila fortunata ♂ (x 95); B. Moschoneura ela xanthella ♂ (x 75); C. Patia c. cordillera ♂ (x 47); D. Patia rethes ♂ (x 32)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1048543/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048549>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. (A – F). Distal antennomeres fused in Dismorphiinae and location of lateral sulci. A. Pseudopontia gola (x 450) where there is a ventral unfinished division; B. Enantia citrinella ♂ (x 200); it can observed the ventral fusion of three antennomeres and the dorsal division between the last distals (two fused); C. Dismorphia eunoe eunoe ♀ (x 350), where there is apparently no fusion of the distal antennomeres; D. Moschoneura pinthous monica ♂ (x 300) where the fusion / division is shown in the distal antennomere; E. Patia cordillera cordillera ♀ (x 170); F. Dorsal view of the scaleless club of Pseudopieris sp. nov. ♀ (x 80) in which it can observed an asymmetric lateral, lateral-dorsal, and dorsal distribution of the lateral sulci." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1048549/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048551>
    dc:description "FIGURE 12. (A – F). Central sulci and pseudosulci in some species of Dismorphiinae. A. Sulcus in the 2 ° antennomere in Leptidea gigantea ♂ (x 451); B. Sulcus in the 2 ° antennomere of L. gigantea ♀ (x 800) irregular outline and near to pseudosulcus; C. Sulcus 6 ° antennomere in Enantia jethys ♂ (x 850), with two pseudosulci; D. Central sulcus (well-defined boundary) in the 2 ° antennomere of Pseudopieris nehemia jessica ♂ (x 900); E. Sulcus in the 3 ° antennomere of Moschoneura pinthous ♂ (x 550); F. Sulcus in the 5 ° antennomere Patia c. cordillera ♀ (x 550)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1048551/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048529>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. (A – H). Structures and sensilla of scaleless antennomeres in Dismorphiinae. A. Second scaleless antennomere of the club in Pseudopieris nehemia prasina ♂; B. Central sulcus (regular outline) of the same antennomere in P. n. prasina ♂. The trichoid sensilla and a chaetic sensilla (outside the sulcus, left) in darkened areas; C. Microtrichia type 1 (m 1) within the sulci, surrounding the trichoid sensilla (Lieinix nemesis athis ♂). There are cuticular pores (pc) at the base of the grooves; D. Microtrichia type 2 (m 2) (L. n athis ♂.), outside the sulci; E. Microtrichia type 3 (m 3) (L. n. athis ♂), around the coeloconic sensilla in some species of Dismorphiinae; F. Typical trichoid sensilla (st) surrounded by microtrichia type 1 (m 1) in Enantia jethys ♀; G. Chaetic sensilla type 1 (sq 1), the most common, present in P. nehemia penia ♀; surrounded by a cuticular collar (cc) interrupted by a notch in a ' V' form; H. Chaetic sensilla type 2 (sq 2) surrounded by microtrichia type 2 (m 2) in Patia c. cordillera ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1048529/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1048533>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. (A – G). Other types of sensilla on the antennae of Dismorphiinae. A. Basiconic sensilla (sb) in Enantia citrinella ♀; B. Basiconic sensilla (sb) in Pseudopieris nehemia jessica ♀, with cuticular pores (pc) and cuticular wall pores (pps) in the top box; C. Auriculate sensilla (sa) in Pseudopieris nehemia jessica ♂; D. Coeloconic sensilla type 1 (sc 1) with distal details d 1 (Moschoneura pinthous patricia ♂), d 2 and d 3 (Patia c. cordillera ♂); E. Coeloconic sensilla type 2 (sc 2) surrounded by smooth and sharp microtrichia type 4 (m 4) in Leptidea morsei ♂; F. Unidentified sensilla 1 (ni 1) in P. n. jessica ♀ surrounded by microtrichia type 2 (m 2); G. Unidentified sensilla 2 (ni 2) in P. n. jessica ♀; microtrichia type 2 (m 2)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1048533/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

